## The Video Games Portal  

**Shortcut:** [P:VG](/P:VG)  

**Portal maintenance status:** The subpages of this portal have been checked and are required for proper navigation. Editors are reminded to exercise [caution](/Wikipedia:CAREFUL) especially when employing scripts or bots. Detailed instructions for refreshing the portal’s maintenance data can be found on the [template page](/Template:Portal_maintenance_status).  

### Overview  

A [video game](/Video_game) , computer game , or simply game , is an [electronic game](/Electronic_game) that involves interaction with a [user interface](/User_interface) or [input device](/Input_device) (such as a [joystick](/Joystick), [controller](/Game_controller), [keyboard](/Computer_keyboard), or [motion sensing](/Motion_sensing) device) to generate [visual](/Visual) [feedback](/Feedback) from a [display device](/Display_device), most commonly shown in a [video](/Video) format on a [television set](/Television_set), [computer monitor](/Computer_monitor), [flat-panel display](/Flat-panel_display) or [touchscreen](/Touchscreen) on [handheld devices](/Handheld_device), or a [virtual reality headset](/Virtual_reality_headset). Most modern video games are [audiovisual](/Audiovisual), with [audio](/Sound) complement delivered through [speakers](/Loudspeaker) or [headphones](/Headphones), and sometimes also with other types of sensory feedback (e.g., [haptic technology](/Haptic_technology) that provides [tactile](/Touch) sensations). Some video games also allow [microphone](/Microphone) and [webcam](/Webcam) inputs for [in-game chatting](/Voice_chat_in_online_gaming) and [livestreaming](/Video_game_livestreaming).  

Video games are typically categorized according to their [hardware platform](/Hardware_platform), which traditionally includes [arcade video games](/Arcade_video_game), [console games](/Console_game), and [computer games](/PC_game) (which includes [LAN games](/Network_game), [online games](/Online_game), and [browser games](/Browser_game)). More recently, the [video game industry](/Video_game_industry) has expanded onto [mobile gaming](/Mobile_gaming) through [mobile devices](/Mobile_device) (such as [smartphones](/Smartphones) and [tablet computers](/Tablet_computers)), [virtual](/Virtual_reality) and [augmented reality](/Augmented_reality) systems, and remote [cloud gaming](/Cloud_gaming). Video games are also classified into a wide range of [genres](/Video_game_genre) based on their style of [gameplay](/Gameplay) and [target audience](/Target_audience). ( [Full article...](/Video_game) )  

