#### Image 1  

*God of War* is a 2005 [action‑adventure game](/Action-adventure_game) developed by [Santa Monica Studio](/Santa_Monica_Studio) and published by [Sony Computer Entertainment](/Sony_Computer_Entertainment) (SCE). First released for the [PlayStation 2](/PlayStation_2) on March 22, 2005, the game is the first installment in the God of War series and the third chronologically. Loosely based on [Greek mythology](/Greek_mythology), it is set in [ancient Greece](/Ancient_Greece) with vengeance as its central motif. The player controls the protagonist [Kratos](/Kratos_(God_of_War)), a [Spartan](/Sparta) warrior who serves the [Olympian gods](/Twelve_Olympians). The goddess [Athena](/Athena) tasks Kratos with killing [Ares](/Ares), the God of War and Kratos’ former mentor who tricked Kratos into killing his wife and daughter. As Ares besieges [Athens](/Classical_Athens) out of hatred for Athena, Kratos embarks on a quest to find the one object capable of stopping the god once and for all: [Pandora's Box](/Pandora%27s_Box).  

The [gameplay](/Gameplay) of God of War focuses on [combo‑based](/Combo_(video_gaming)) combat, achieved through the player’s main weapon—the Blades of Chaos—and a secondary weapon acquired later in the game. It features [quick time events](/Quick_time_event) that require the player to complete various game controller actions in a timed sequence to defeat stronger enemies and [bosses](/Boss_(video_gaming)). The player can use up to four magical attacks and a power‑enhancing ability as alternative combat options. It also features [puzzles](/Puzzle_video_game) and [platforming](/Platform_game) elements.  

God of War received critical acclaim, being highly praised for its graphics, sound, story, and gameplay and has been cited as one of the [greatest video games ever made](/List_of_video_games_considered_the_best). Regarded as one of the best action‑adventure games for the platform, God of War won several "Game of the Year" awards. In 2009, entertainment website [IGN](/IGN) named God of War the seventh‑best PlayStation 2 game of all time. The game sold over 4.6 million units by June 2012, making it the [12th best‑selling PlayStation 2 game of all time](/List_of_best-selling_PlayStation_2_video_games). The success of the game led to the development of eight more games and expansion into other media. The game and its first sequel, [God of War II](/God_of_War_II) , were remastered and released in November 2009 as the [God of War Collection](/God_of_War_video_game_collections) , and in 2012, the remastered version was re‑released as part of the [God of War Saga](/God_of_War_video_game_collections) , both for the [PlayStation 3](/PlayStation_3). God of War Collection was later ported to the [PlayStation Vita](/PlayStation_Vita) in 2014. A [novelization](/Novelization) of the game was published in May 2010, and a [film adaptation](/Film_adaptation) had been in development for many years but was ultimately canceled. ( [Full article...](/God_of_War_(2005_video_game)) )  

