[Kim Kitsuragi](/Kim_Kitsuragi) is a character in the 2019 detective video game [Disco Elysium](/Disco_Elysium). As a [non‑playable companion character](/Non-player_character), he assists the [player character](/Player_character) in solving a murder that comprises the game's main plot. Kitsuragi is defined by his Asian‑inspired background, private [queerness](/Queer), and calm, [stoic](/Stoicism) personality. He was noted by journalists and academics for his reactions to the player's choices, ranging from [deadpan](/Deadpan) quips to moments of approval and vulnerability.  

Kitsuragi was designed by the [Estonian](/Estonia) studio [ZA/UM](/ZA/UM) under the direction of [Robert Kurvitz](/Robert_Kurvitz). The writer had previously developed the fictional setting for a novel and [tabletop role‑playing](/Tabletop_role-playing_game) sessions. The team wanted to innovate on typical [dialog trees](/Dialogue_tree) seen in [role‑playing video games](/Role-playing_video_game), deciding to only reveal aspects of Kitsuragi's character in specific situations. They decided that the character should have a "vaguely French" accent, leading them to cast the actor Jullian Champenois for his voice performance.  

Kim Kitsuragi received acclaim as a standout character from Disco Elysium . Critics highlighted his subtle responses, moral integrity, and endearing presence, describing how his interactions contributed to the game's most memorable moments. Kitsuragi was celebrated as one of the best video game characters of 2019, with journalists noting his exceptional writing, design, and [performance](/Voice_acting). His portrayal is recognized for reflecting Disco Elysium ’s themes and offering a nuanced representation of queer and cultural experiences. ( [Full article...](/Kim_Kitsuragi) )  

