**Image 2** – Carmack in 2025  

[John D. Carmack II](/John_Carmack) (born August 21, 1970) is an American [computer programmer](/Computer_programmer) and [video‑game developer](/Video_game_developer). He co‑founded the video‑game company [id Software](/Id_Software) and was the lead programmer of its 1990s games [Commander Keen](/Commander_Keen) , [Wolfenstein 3D](/Wolfenstein_3D) , [Doom](/Doom_(1993_video_game)) , [Quake](/Quake_(video_game)) , and their sequels. Carmack made innovations in [3D computer graphics](/3D_computer_graphics), such as his Carmack's Reverse algorithm for [shadow volumes](/Shadow_volume).  

In 2013, he resigned from id Software to work full‑time at [Oculus VR](/Reality_Labs) as their [CTO](/Chief_technology_officer). In 2019, he reduced his role to Consulting CTO so he could allocate more time toward [artificial general intelligence](/Artificial_general_intelligence) (AGI). In 2022, he left Oculus to work on his AGI startup, Keen Technologies. ( [Full article...](/John_D._Carmack) )  

