**Image 3** – Meier at the 2010 Game Developers Conference  

[Sidney K. Meier](/Sid_Meier) ([/ˈmaɪər/](/Help:IPA/English) MIRE ; born February 24, 1954) is an American businessman and computer programmer. A [programmer](/Game_programmer), [designer](/Game_designer), and [producer](/Video_game_producer) of many [strategy](/Strategy_video_game) and [simulation](/Simulation_video_game) video games, including the [Civilization](/Civilization_(series)) series, Meier co‑founded [MicroProse](/MicroProse) in 1982 with [Bill Stealey](/Bill_Stealey) and is the Director of Creative Development of [Firaxis Games](/Firaxis_Games), which he co‑founded with [Jeff Briggs](/Jeff_Briggs) and [Brian Reynolds](/Brian_Reynolds_(game_designer)) in 1996. For his contributions to the [video‑game industry](/Video_game_industry), Meier was inducted into the [Academy of Interactive Arts and Sciences](/Academy_of_Interactive_Arts_and_Sciences) Hall of Fame. ( [Full article...](/Sid_Meier) )  

