**Image 4** – Inafune at Japan Expo 2012  

[Keiji Inafune](/Keiji_Inafune) (稲船 敬二, Inafune Keiji ; born 8 May 1965) is a Japanese [video‑game producer](/Video_game_producer), character designer, game designer, and businessman. In 2009, he was chosen by [IGN](/IGN) as one of the top 100 game creators of all time.  

Starting his career at [Capcom](/Capcom) in the late 1980s, his job was as an artist and illustrator. The first two games he worked on were the original [Street Fighter](/Street_Fighter_(video_game)) and Mega Man in 1987. He was then a character designer and planner of the [Mega Man](/Mega_Man) series during the [NES](/NES) and [Super NES](/Super_NES) era. For [Mega Man X](/Mega_Man_X) , he created and designed the character [Zero](/Zero_(Mega_Man)). ( [Full article...](/Keiji_Inafune) )  

