**Image 5** – Roberta Williams in 2022  

[Roberta Lynn Williams](/Roberta_Williams) ([née](/Birth_name) Heuer ; born February 16, 1953) is an American [video‑game designer](/Video_game_designer) and [writer](/Video_game_writer). She has been named by several publications as one of the best or most influential creators in the [video‑game industry](/Video_game_industry).  

Williams co‑founded [Sierra On‑Line](/Sierra_Entertainment) with her husband, [game developer](/Video_game_developer) [Ken Williams](/Ken_Williams_(game_developer)). In 1980, her first game, [Mystery House](/Mystery_House) , became a modest commercial success; it is credited as the first [graphic adventure game](/Adventure_game). She then became known for creating and maintaining the [King's Quest](/King%27s_Quest) series, as well as designing the [full motion video](/Full-motion_video) game [Phantasmagoria](/Phantasmagoria_(video_game)) in 1995. Sierra was acquired by [CUC International](/CUC_International) in 1996, leading to layoffs and management changes. Williams took a brief [sabbatical](/Sabbatical), and returned to the company in a game‑design role, but grew increasingly frustrated with CUC's creative and business decisions. ( [Full article...](/Roberta_Williams) )  

