**Image 8** – Wright speaking at the 2010 Game Developers Conference  

[William Ralph Wright](/Will_Wright_(game_designer)) (born January 20, 1960) is an American [video‑game designer](/Video_game_designer) and co‑founder of the [game development](/Video_game_developer) company [Maxis](/Maxis), which later became part of [Electronic Arts](/Electronic_Arts). In April 2009, he left EA to run Stupid Fun Club Camp, an entertainment [think tank](/Think_tank) in which Wright and EA are principal shareholders.  

The first computer game Wright designed was [Raid on Bungeling Bay](/Raid_on_Bungeling_Bay) in 1984, but it was [SimCity](/SimCity_(1989_video_game)) that brought him to prominence. The game was published by Maxis, which Wright co‑formed with Jeff Braun. Wright continued to innovate on the game's central theme of [simulation](/Computer_simulation) with numerous other titles including [SimEarth](/SimEarth) and [SimAnt](/SimAnt) . ( [Full article...](/Will_Wright_(game_designer)) )  

