**Image 9** – Morhaime at BlizzCon 2009  

[Michael Morhaime](/Michael_Morhaime) (born November 3, 1967) is an American [video‑game developer](/Video_game_developer) and entrepreneur. He is the chief executive officer (CEO) and founder of [Dreamhaven](/Dreamhaven), located in [Irvine, California](/Irvine,_California). Morhaime is best known as the co‑founder and the former [president](/President_(corporate_title)) of [Blizzard Entertainment](/Blizzard_Entertainment), a subsidiary of [Activision Blizzard, Inc](/Activision_Blizzard)., that was founded in 1991 as Silicon & Synapse. He served on the Vivendi Games executive committee from January 1999, when Blizzard Entertainment, Inc. became a subsidiary of Vivendi Games, until July 2008. ( [Full article...](/Michael_Morhaime) )  

