**Image 10** – Hale in March 2024  

[Jennifer Hale](/Jennifer_Hale) is a Canadian and American voice actress. She is well known for her work in video‑game franchises such as [Baldur's Gate](/Baldur%27s_Gate) , [Mass Effect](/Mass_Effect) , [Metal Gear Solid](/Metal_Gear_(series)) , [BioShock Infinite](/BioShock_Infinite) , [Metroid Prime](/Metroid_Prime) , [Halo](/Halo_(franchise)) , [Overwatch](/Overwatch_(video_game)) , and [Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic](/Star_Wars:_Knights_of_the_Old_Republic) . In 2013, she was recognized by [Guinness World Records](/Guinness_World_Records) as the most prolific video‑game voice actor, which she held until it was broken by [Lani Minella](/Lani_Minella) in 2024.  

Hale is featured in animation such as [The Real Adventures of Jonny Quest](/The_Real_Adventures_of_Jonny_Quest) , [The Powerpuff Girls](/The_Powerpuff_Girls) , [Codename: Kids Next Door](/Codename:_Kids_Next_Door) , [The Grim Adventures of Billy & Mandy](/The_Grim_Adventures_of_Billy_%26_Mandy) , [Brandy & Mr. Whiskers](/Brandy_%26_Mr._Whiskers) , [Totally Spies!](/Totally_Spies!) , [Avatar: The Last Airbender](/Avatar:_The_Last_Airbender) and its continuation [The Legend of Korra](/The_Legend_of_Korra) , [Where on Earth Is Carmen Sandiego?](/Where_on_Earth_Is_Carmen_Sandiego%3F) and [Star Wars: The Clone Wars](/Star_Wars:_The_Clone_Wars_(2008_TV_series)) . She also voices Thorn of the [Hex Girls](/The_Hex_Girls) in various [Scooby‑Doo](/Scooby-Doo) movies and TV episodes, as well as [Cinderella](/Cinderella_(Disney_character)) and [Princess Aurora](/Aurora_(Disney)) in various [Disney Princess](/Disney_Princess) media of the 2000s and 2010s. She is also known for voicing [Jean Grey](/Jean_Grey) in a variety of [Marvel](/Marvel_Comics) media, most recently in [X‑Men '97](/X-Men_%2797) (2024–present). ( [Full article...](/Jennifer_Hale) )  

