**Image 13** – Pajitnov in 2024  

[Alexey Leonidovich Pajitnov](/Alexey_Pajitnov) (born April 16, 1955) is a [Russian‑American](/Russian_Americans) [computer engineer](/Computer_engineering) and [video‑game designer](/Video_game_design). He is best known for creating, designing, and developing [Tetris](/Tetris) in 1985 while working at the [Dorodnitsyn Computing Centre](/Dorodnitsyn_Computing_Centre) under the [Academy of Sciences of the Soviet Union](/Academy_of_Sciences_of_the_Soviet_Union) (now the [Russian Academy of Sciences](/Russian_Academy_of_Sciences)). After Tetris was released internationally in 1987, he released a sequel in 1989, entitled [Welltris](/Welltris) .  

In 1991, he moved to the United States and later became a U.S. citizen. In 1996, Pajitnov founded [The Tetris Company](/The_Tetris_Company) alongside Dutch video‑game designer [Henk Rogers](/Henk_Rogers). Despite the game's high popularity, Pajitnov did not receive [royalties](/Royalties) from Tetris prior to this time; [the Soviet Union had disintegrated by 1991](/Dissolution_of_the_Soviet_Union). ( [Full article...](/Alexey_Pajitnov) )  

