**Image 15** – Akira Toriyama  

[Akira Toriyama](/Akira_Toriyama) ([Japanese](/Japanese_language): 鳥山明, [Hepburn](/Hepburn_romanization): Toriyama Akira ; April 5, 1955 – March 1, 2024) was a Japanese [manga artist](/Manga_artist) and character designer. He is widely regarded as one of the greatest and most influential authors in the [history of manga](/History_of_manga) and created numerous highly influential and popular series, with his most famous being Dragon Ball .  

Toriyama first achieved mainstream recognition for creating the [manga](/Manga) series [Dr. Slump](/Dr._Slump) , for which he earned the 1981 [Shogakukan Manga Award](/Shogakukan_Manga_Award) for best [shōnen](/Sh%C5%8Dnen_manga) / shōjo . Dr. Slump went on to sell over 35 million copies in Japan. It was adapted into an [anime](/Anime), with a second series created in 1997, 13 years after the manga ended. ( [Full article...](/Akira_Toriyama) )  

