**Image 16** – Tomohiro Nishikado  

[Tomohiro Nishikado](/Tomohiro_Nishikado) (西角 友宏, Nishikado Tomohiro ; born March 31, 1944) is a Japanese [video‑game developer](/Video_game_developer) and [engineer](/Engineer). He is the creator of the arcade [shoot 'em up](/Shoot_%27em_up) game [Space Invaders](/Space_Invaders) , released to the public in 1978 by the [Taito Corporation](/Taito_Corporation) of [Japan](/Japan), often credited as the first shoot 'em up and for beginning the [golden age of arcade video games](/Golden_age_of_arcade_video_games). Prior to Space Invaders , he also designed other earlier Taito arcade games, including the shooting [electro‑mechanical games](/Electro-mechanical_game) Sky Fighter (1971) and Sky Fighter II , the [sports video game](/Sports_video_game) TV Basketball in 1974, the [vertical scrolling](/Vertical_scrolling) [racing video game](/Racing_video_game) [Speed Race](/Speed_Race) (also known as Wheels ) in 1974, the [multi‑directional shooter](/Multi-directional_shooter) [Western Gun](/Gun_Fight) (also known as Gun Fight ) in 1975, and the first‑person [combat flight simulator](/Combat_flight_simulator) Interceptor (1975). ( [Full article...](/Tomohiro_Nishikado) )  

