**Image 18** – Jeremy Soule  

[Jeremy Soule](/Jeremy_Soule) ([/soʊl/](/Help:IPA/English) SOHL ; born December 19, 1975) is an American composer of soundtracks for film, television, and video games. He has composed soundtracks for over 60 games and over a dozen other works during his career, including [The Elder Scrolls](/The_Elder_Scrolls) , [Guild Wars](/Guild_Wars) , [Total Annihilation](/Total_Annihilation) , and the [Harry Potter](/Harry_Potter_video_games) series.  

He became an employee of [Square](/Square_(video_game_company)) in 1994 after several years of private composition studies. After finishing the soundtrack to [Secret of Evermore](/Secret_of_Evermore) in 1995, he left to join [Humongous Entertainment](/Humongous_Entertainment), where he composed for several children's games as well as [Total Annihilation](/Total_Annihilation) , his first award‑winning score. In 2000, he left to form his own music production company, Soule Media, later called Artistry Entertainment. In 2005, he founded DirectSong, a record label that published digital versions of his soundtracks as well as those of classical composers. DirectSong remained active until 2019. ( [Full article...](/Jeremy_Soule) )  

