**Image 19** – Persson at the 2016 Game Developers Conference  

[Markus Alexej Persson](/Markus_Persson) ([/ˈpɪərsən/](/Help:IPA/English)&#32; [ⓘ](/File:Markus_Persson_Pronunciation_in_American_English.ogg) PEER‑sən , Swedish: [&#91;ˈmǎrːkɵs ˈpæ̌ːʂɔn&#93;](/Help:IPA/Swedish) [ⓘ](/File:Sv-Markus_Persson.ogg) ; born 1 June 1979), known by the pseudonym Notch , is a Swedish [video‑game programmer](/Video_game_programmer) and [designer](/Video_game_designer). He is the creator of [Minecraft](/Minecraft) , which is the [best‑selling video game in history](/List_of_best-selling_video_games). He founded the video‑game development company [Mojang Studios](/Mojang_Studios) in 2009.  

Persson began developing video games at an early age. His commercial success began after he published an early version of Minecraft in 2009. Prior to the game's official retail release in 2011, it had sold over four million copies. After this point Persson stood down as the lead designer and transferred his creative authority to [Jens Bergensten](/Jens_Bergensten). In September 2014 Persson announced on his personal website that he had concluded he "[didn't have the connection to his fans he thought he had]", that he had "become a symbol", and that he did not wish to be responsible for Mojang's increasingly large operation. He left Mojang in November of that year, selling his company to [Microsoft](/Microsoft) reportedly for US$2.5 billion, which made him a [billionaire](/Billionaire). ( [Full article...](/Markus_Persson) )  

