**Image 23** – Bushnell in 2013  

[Nolan Kay Bushnell](/Nolan_Bushnell) (born February 5, 1943) is an American businessman and electrical engineer. He established [Atari, Inc.](/Atari,_Inc.) and the [Chuck E. Cheese's Pizza Time Theatre](/Chuck_E._Cheese) chain. He has been inducted into the [Video Game Hall of Fame](/Walk_of_Game) and the [Consumer Electronics Association](/Consumer_Electronics_Association) Hall of Fame, received the [BAFTA](/BAFTA) Fellowship and the Nations Restaurant News "Innovator of the Year" award and was named one of [Newsweek](/Newsweek) 's "50 Men Who Changed America". He has started more than 20 companies and is one of the founding fathers of the [video‑game industry](/Video_game_industry). He is on the board of Anti‑Aging Games. In 2012, he founded an educational software company called Brainrush that uses [video‑game](/Video_game) technology in educational software.  

He is credited with [Bushnell's Law](/Bushnell%27s_Law), an [aphorism](/Aphorism) about games that are "easy to learn and difficult to master" being rewarding. ( [Full article...](/Nolan_Bushnell) )  

