### Recent video‑game‑related events  

September 29, 2025 – [American](/Video_games_in_the_United_States) [video‑game company](/Video_game_company) [Electronic Arts](/Electronic_Arts) (EA) agrees to be acquired by a group of private investors, including [Silver Lake](/Silver_Lake_(investment_firm)), the [Public Investment Fund](/Public_Investment_Fund) of [Saudi Arabia](/Saudi_Arabia) and [Affinity Partners](/Affinity_Partners), in a deal valued at $55 billion. The transaction, which will take EA [private](/Privately_held_company), constitutes the largest [leveraged buyout](/Leveraged_buyout) on record. (Bloomberg News)  

June 5, 2025 – [Nintendo](/Nintendo)'s [Switch 2](/Nintendo_Switch_2) [video‑game console](/Video_game_console) is released in most regions. (BBC News) ( The Verge )  

